The paper deals with the problem of releasing statistics about a sensitive social network while preserving privacy of its participants. This falls under the domain of data privacy and security, which is covered by the cs.CR sub-category. The paper also deals with graph statistics, which is a topic covered by the cs.DS sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses differential privacy, which is a technique covered by the cs.SI sub-category. The paper also involves tradeoffs between privacy and utility, which is a topic covered by the cs.IT sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a solution that involves upper bounds on maximum degree, which is a topic covered by the cs.LG sub-category.
